social_posts.post_text: I’m waking up and about to to go see some of South Africa today, so I will post later about what God did last night. But for now, a testimony 👆🏻and a quick update: I woke up unable to go back to sleep as I was filled with joy and fire of God for what He did last night. I’ve never seen Him move so powerfully! There were thousands who came, from several countries in Africa, Europe and India…around 2,500-3000. Thousands sooo hungry and in love with Jesus. Jesus filled the hungry, moving in the most shocking power, setting free so many of all ages! I’m in awe of Jesus! He’s so good! He’s so faithful! He’s all powerful! THANK YOU JESUS!!!!! 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🇿🇦❤️

Revival is Now South Africa was a move of God like I’ve never seen! 🇿🇦🔥2,500-3,000 people came to the event in Johannesburg area; many traveling from several different countries. The hunger was massive! God showed up in in power like I’ve never seen! Person after person was delivered by the power of God; all ages. I’m overwhelmed by all of the testimonies people have shared. Jesus did so many miracles for His people. Many testimonies share of healing, deliverance, impartation and encounters with God happening all over the room; Jesus touching people right where they were! We shouted “JESUS, JESUS, JESUS” at the end, praising Him for all that He did, at the top of our lungs, and thousands of those voices together made a loud, thunderous praise; sounding like a sports stadium cheering, but it was for JESUS! 😭 What a glorious sound it was!!! I am absolutely in awe of Jesus and so humbled by what He has done at Revival is Now South Africa. People of SA & all who traveled from other countries - I’m so touched by your hunger. Thank you for your love and hunger for Jesus! Thank you Jesus for all of the uncountable miracles you’ve done for your people! I’m already so excited for the next Revival is Now South Africa! 🇿🇦

I am so grateful to God for all He has done in 2022! This year God’s revival has grown & spread across the world! The word has spread more & more that Jesus is alive & moving in power; healing every kind of sickness & casting out every demon! In the beginning of 2022 I endured the most difficult persecution I had experienced so far in ministry. This wasn’t easy but it was a gift, because it was an opportunity for my heart to be refined to be more Christlike. It was an opportunity to show God’s love & His reflection more; to love my enemies & to respond to accusations with grace. It was an opportunity to trust God more; to believe that He was my defender & would protect me. I am grateful for these opportunities because by the end of 2022 I can say that I have been refined more, my faith has grown & I’ve seen a new level of God’s faithfulness that I hadn’t seen yet. I saw the word come alive in my life “there are more for you than against you.” I saw God’s hand over me & my ministry. The work of God continued and grew! I ministered in different states & nations almost every week of 2022. This year God sent me on my 1st international ministry trip & there have been a total of 12 of them since (10 nations)! This year I’ve ministered at 56 cities & have ministered at 89 Revival is Now events/services, always returning to LA for every Sunday service at @5fchurch. At @5fchurch in 2022 many traveled from other nations as well as each week we’ve had guests traveling from other states to encounter God. God has done uncountable miracles. He has delivered & healed so many. The revival has spread as many have received impartation & are walking in the power of God in their cities. I am so grateful to God for all He has done. I’ve learned this year that no matter how scary the Goliath looks, there is NOTHING to fear when God is on your side! Rest in Him as He fights your battles & stay focused with the assignment He’s given you whether you’re on the mountain top or the valley! Keep doing God’s work, keep trusting, keep being victorious over the devil! 🔥❤️ I’m so excited for all that God has in store for 2023!

WE ARE IN THE END-TIME REVIVAL! 🔥 And we’ve got work to do! The End-time revival doesn’t mean ‘sit around and wait for Jesus to return.’ It means we have to get to work and prepare ourselves. We have to be obedient to the Holy Spirit and allow Him to transform us & beautify us! This is the revival of the BRIDE BEING PREPARED & TRANSFORMED! This means: it’s time to look and be like the Acts Church. 🔥

Characteristics of the Acts Church:
✅ Five-Fold ministry welcomed in the body and operating in the body to equip the body. Apostles and Prophets must be welcomed and restored back in the church. 
✅ The Holy Spirit must be welcomed in all of His ways: the Holy Spirit who makes demons tremble and leave, the Holy Spirit who baptizes in fire & gives heavenly languages, the Holy Spirit who manifests however He wants (people falling back with God’s power, overflowing and laughing with joy, etc). 
✅ God’s true anointed vessels must be accepted rather than the self-appointed. (And God’s anointed will be the unlikely…the foolish things to confound the wisdom of this world. Remember the disciples: fishermen, tax collectors…)
✅ The fear of God must be in the church. There must be a reverence for God and His work. Church cannot be a social function/activity/entertainment/place to show off your clothes and flirt. God and His work in the church must be revered and respected. Motives must be pure. If the Holy Spirit wants church to last 3 hours, then we respect that. God and His work must be our priority! 

Revelation 19:7
Let us rejoice and be glad and give him glory! For the wedding of the Lamb has come, and his bride has made herself ready.

Watch the full message “The End-time Revival” here: https://www.youtube.com/live/rjDHOd0y0FQ?feature=share

Today is the 2 year anniversary of when revival broke out in the park at @5fchurch; the day that God used me to cast out a demon for the very 1st time. This video shows the 1st deliverance and how revival broke out from there. 2 months from 3/21/21, 300 came to our service in the park and so many were set free and touched by God. It was revival beyond what I had dreamed! Since that day hundreds have traveled from different states and countries to encounter God at @5fchurch in LA every single week. Since the 1st deliverance there have been 130 Revival events in 87 cities and 11 nations, where thousands have been set free, healed and touched by God.

I’ll never forget 3/21/21. I remember vividly driving to the park that day, more expectant than EVER! Because 2 different people wrote to me that they were flying across the country to come to our service in the park (they had seen videos of mine online that first went viral 2 months prior). We only had 20-30 people coming to our church in the park at that time so I was SHOCKED! I knew God’s principle of hunger: the more hunger, the more God can do! So with this amount of hunger for 4 people to be flying across the nation, I knew God was going to move so powerfully; but even then, I had no clue He was going to move so powerfully that a demon would manifest and be cast out. I had no idea that what He did that day would change EVERYTHING! It was a suddenly moment of promises fulfilled; promises I had been believing in and waiting on for 4.5 years. After this day, my heart burst of this bigger revelation I had of God’s faithfulness. I wanted to shout on the rooftops GOD IS FAITHFUL. As I reflect back on this day, I am reminded that God is a God who does exceedingly, abundantly above all that we ask of think and that HE IS SO FAITHFUL. All His promises really do come to pass! 

Thank you Jesus for being revival! Thank you for Your precious anointing that destroys yokes and delivers your children from the bondage of the devil! Thank you Jesus for Your hand upon Your move. Thank you for defeating all of the devil’s attacks against Your revival! 

REVIVAL IS NOW & the best is yet to come! 🔥Glory to God for everything!

What the relationship of Christians & Politics should be:
Christians should take part as citizens to vote for Christlike policies. But Christians should not make policies, laws, political leaders & parties an IDOL, where they put more faith in the politics than in Jesus & His power. The faith should be in God’s spirit to bring change to the nation, not faith in the “might” of politics. Christians need to realize that the real world changing power is within themselves when they truly carry God’s power & make it their every day mission to love people with God’s love and allow His power to flow through them. When your favorite political candidate doesn’t win an election, it should not shake you or even upset you! The real power is not in politics but by God’s power through the body of Christ - bringing salvation to person after person; therefore person after person will become Christlike and choose to live morally right and then the country/world will be truly transformed! 

Watch the whole message on my YouTube or Five-Fold Church YouTube titled “The Global Gospel.”

To be effective in casting out demons you have to be executing authority properly because demons go based on the authority you have over them. What makes demons leave is:
1. They see you have authority over them
2. They see you know you have authority over them
3. They see you executing your authority over them PROPERLY

Many are not effective in casting out demons because they aren’t operating in the realm of authority, but rather are trying to cast out demons in whatever way they feel, with different methods and based on tradition (what they’ve seen others do). 

In the Bible we see all demons and sicknesses obeying the authority of Apostle Peter (authority in Christ). They would all leave as soon as they entered Peter’s territory in Christ. (Acts 5:15-16) God wants us to be as effective as Peter was in the body of Christ today - but we have to follow God’s order and His principles of how to cast out demons.

How to give all the glory to God when you minister! 🙏🏻‼️

Ministers, don’t beckon the congregation to give you applause whether it’s trying to get amens, or trying to have the people be impressed with your prophetic gift and anointing. Don’t turn the precious ministry of Jesus into a show by doing “too much” that wasn’t necessary to cast the demon out or to deliver the prophetic word. As we minister we should have the heart that we want all awe and wonder to be towards God, not “our gifts.” When one does “extra” to get a “rise” out of the people, they have crossed over to the place of desiring some of the glory for themselves. It doesn’t mean there can’t be different styles and different ways to prophecy and cast out demons. It’s about the motive. As you minister, have the heart and the fear of God for all the glory to go to Him.

Understanding how a “Judas” comes to be. 

Imagine the narrative that would be going around when news spread that one of the 12 closest disciples and the one in charge of finances left Jesus and turned him into the authorities. “He must be guilty. He must be false like people are saying. The rumors about Jesus must be true,” could’ve been some of the thoughts and words that were going around after hearing of what Judas did. As there was a Judas in the time of Jesus, there are Judas’s of today as well. It’s important as a believer to be aware of this reality, so you won’t be deceived by thoughts the enemy may try to plant through the actions of a present day “Judas.” It’s also important to know how a “Judas” comes to be, so you don’t become one (no one should be so prideful to think that they’re automatically immune to becoming a Judas).
